issues.description:
In the ReadableStream catch block, when an LLM error occurs mid-stream (after first token), the code sends `data: [ERROR]

` but doesn't save any partial assistant message. This is acceptable behavior (partial responses shouldn't be persisted), but the client has no structured way to distinguish an error event from the DONE event. Consider using a JSON error payload like `data: {"error": "stream interrupted"}

` for consistency.
